TITLE: Using flip middleware for automatic placement adjustment
DESCRIPTION: Implements the flip middleware to automatically adjust the tooltip's placement when it doesn't fit in the viewport.
SOURCE: https://github.com/floating-ui/floating-ui/blob/master/website/pages/docs/tutorial.mdx#2025-04-23_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import {
  computePosition,
  flip,
} from 'https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@floating-ui/dom@__DOM_VERSION__/+esm';

const button = document.querySelector('#button');
const tooltip = document.querySelector('#tooltip');

computePosition(button, tooltip, {
  placement: 'top',
  middleware: [flip()],
}).then(({x, y}) => {
  Object.assign(tooltip.style, {
    left: `${x}px`,
    top: `${y}px`,
  });
});
```

