TITLE: Handling Tooltips on Disabled Buttons in React
DESCRIPTION: Creates a modified Button component that remains accessible to tooltip events even when visually disabled. Uses aria-disabled instead of the disabled attribute to maintain event handling capabilities.
SOURCE: https://github.com/floating-ui/floating-ui/blob/master/website/pages/docs/tooltip.mdx#2025-04-23_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
const Button = React.forwardRef(function Button(
  {visuallyDisabled, disabled, ...props},
  ref,
) {
  return (
    <button
      {...props}
      ref={ref}
      disabled={visuallyDisabled ? undefined : disabled}
      aria-disabled={visuallyDisabled ? 'true' : undefined}
      // You'll want to do this for all relevant event handlers.
      onClick={visuallyDisabled ? undefined : props.onClick}
    />
  );
});
```

