TITLE: Using Event Communication Between Hooks in Floating UI
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to use the event emitter attached to the context object to communicate between hooks. The example demonstrates subscribing to events with on/off methods and emitting events with custom data.
SOURCE: https://github.com/floating-ui/floating-ui/blob/master/website/pages/docs/custom-hooks.mdx#2025-04-23_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const {context} = useFloating();

useEffect(() => {
  const handleEvent = () => {};
  context.events.on('name', handleEvent);
  return () => {
    context.events.off('name', handleEvent);
  };
}, [context.events]);

return (
  <div
    onClick={() => {
      context.events.emit('name', {foo: 'bar'});
    }}
  />
);
```

