TITLE: Implementing a Custom 'center' Placement Wrapper in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to abstract the custom centering logic into a reusable wrapper function. It shows the desired simplified API call (`placement: 'center'`) and then provides an implementation (`computePosition` wrapper) that intercepts the 'center' placement option. The wrapper internally uses the `offset` middleware with the centering logic and applies it conditionally, falling back to the base `computePosition` for other placements.
SOURCE: https://github.com/floating-ui/floating-ui/blob/master/website/pages/docs/offset.mdx#2025-04-23_snippet_18

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
computePosition(referenceEl, floatingEl, {
  placement: 'center',
});
```

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import {computePosition as base, offset} from '@floating-ui/dom';

const centerOffset = offset(({rects}) => {
  return -rects.reference.height / 2 - rects.floating.height / 2;
});

export function computePosition(
  referenceEl,
  floatingEl,
  options,
) {
  const isCentered = options.placement === 'center';
  const placement = isCentered ? 'bottom' : options.placement;
  const middleware = [
    isCentered && centerOffset,
    ...(options.middleware || []),
  ];

  return base(referenceEl, floatingEl, {
    ...options,
    placement,
    middleware,
  });
}
```

